{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-21T15:30:55.867Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":1},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Validating Outputs in Reliability Techniques"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Validating outputs"},{"type":"text","text":" is the practice of checking that Claude's responses match your expected schema before using them downstream — a safety step to catch malformed JSON or missing fields that could break your application."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What It Is"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Validating outputs means applying "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"schema validation"},{"type":"text","text":" to Claude's responses after receiving them, ensuring:\n- ✅ JSON is syntactically valid (no "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"JSON.parse()"},{"type":"text","text":" errors)\n- ✅ All required fields exist\n- ✅ Field types match (e.g., "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"age"},{"type":"text","text":" is an integer, not a string)\n- ✅ No unexpected extra fields"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why It Matters"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Even with structured outputs, validation is important because:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Risk"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Without Validation"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"With Validation"}]}]}]},{"type":"